The paper discusses methods for dimensionality reduction and matrix decomposition, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision. The use of sparse representations and clustering also suggests a focus on optimization and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
